fields.description:
We would like to use GitLink (see [https://github.com/GitTools/GitLink]) for our .NET development. Unfortunately that is not possible with BitBucket Server as GitLink (or better say SRCSRV) cannot support question marks in raw file URL.

-BSERV-4036- improved raw file URL so "raw" specification can be now part of path.

Would it be possible to do the same with revision parameter?

E.g. originally we could get raw file for specific version via this:
{code:java}
http://host/projects/{project}/repos/{repo}/browse/path/to/file.ext?at={revision}&raw

{code}
after -BSERV-4036- we can get this:
{code:java}
http://host/projects/{project}/repos/{repo}/raw/path/to/file.ext?at={revision}

{code}
but for GitLink (and everything related to SRCSRV) we would need something like this:
{code:java}
http://host/projects/{project}/repos/{repo}/rawrevision/{revision}/path/to/file.ext

{code}

h3. Problem Definition
The [Connecting Bitbucket Server to PostgreSQL|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BitbucketServer/Connecting+Bitbucket+Server+to+PostgreSQL] documentation currently mentions the following:
{quote}
When you create a PostgreSQL database, a 'public' schema is created and set as the default for that database. It is possible to create a different schema (e.g. 'bitbucket') and set that as the default schema. Bitbucket Server will use whatever schema is set as the default for the logged-in user.
{quote}
This does not seem to explicitly mention that in order for Bitbucket Server to connect, the database must use the default public schema.

h3. Suggested Solution
Update the documentation with the required details. As example the following could be used:
{quote}
It is not possible to use a different schema (e.g. 'bitbucket'). You must use the default public schema.
{quote}

Some URL's referenced in the document [Securing Bitbucket Server behind nginx using SSL|https://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=776640112] do not reflect what these URL's should actually be set to, therefore the following need to be changed:

h4.Under "Step 2: Set a context path for Bitbucket Server"
Change from:
{quote}
For the example configuration on this page, we want Bitbucket Server to be accessed at: 

https://mycompany.com:7990/bitbucket 
{quote}

to:
{quote}
For the example configuration on this page, we want Bitbucket Server to be accessed at: 

https://mycompany.com/bitbucket 
{quote}

h4.Under "Step 3: Change Bitbucket Server's base URL"
Change from:
{quote}
For this example, use  http://mycompany.com:7990/bitbucket   (Note the context path included with this.)
{quote}

to:
{quote}
For this example, use  http://mycompany.com/bitbucket   (Note the context path included with this.)
{quote}

